        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 1:08PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 108 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 9 miles east of Clarksville to 5 miles
south of Purley, or extending from 9 miles east of Clarksville to 6
miles northeast of Winnsboro, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant, Winnsboro, Clarksville, Boxelder, Hagansport,
Mount Vernon, De Kalb, Naples, Bogata, Omaha, Wilkerson, Dalby
Springs, Us 259 And I 30 Intersection, Cookville, Bagwell, Purley,
Winfield, Talco, Avery and Annona.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
